    • Constructor Detail

      • ACLMessage

        public ACLMessage(int performative)
        Creates a new ACL Message. The fields replyWith and inReplyTo are not needed, but all other should be not null.
        Parameters:
        performative - A valid ACL_* value
        sender - Reference to the agent that sent this message
        receiver - Reference to the agent that will receive this message

    • Method Detail

      • getPerformative

        public int getPerformative()
        Communication performative represents the intent of the message. The value of this field is one of the following:
      • ACL_ACCEPT_PROPOSAL
      • ACL_AGREE
      • ACL_CANCEL
      • ACL_CALL_FOR_PROPOSAL
      • ACL_CONFIRM
      • ACL_DISCONFIRM
      • ACL_FAILURE
      • ACL_INFORM
      • ACL_INFORM_IF
      • ACL_INFORM_REF
      • ACL_NOT_UNDERSTOOD
      • ACL_PROPAGATE
      • ACL_PROPOSE
      • ACL_PROXY
      • ACL_QUERY_IF
      • ACL_QUERY_REF
      • ACL_REFUSE
      • ACL_REJECT_PROPOSAL
      • ACL_REQUEST
      • ACL_REQUEST_WHEN
      • ACL_REQUEST_WHENEVER
      • ACL_SUBSCRIBE
Returns:
The performative

  • match

    public boolean match(ACLMessage template)
    This methods expects a "template", which is basically an ACLMessage with part or all of its fields set. All template's fields are compared to this message's. Null values on the template are ignored. The performative "null" value, since it's an integer, is "-1" or ACL.NO_PERFORMATIVE.
    Parameters:
    template -
    Returns:
    True if all fields (expected those ignored) match the template's.
